---
import Article from "../../../layouts/Article.astro";
import KeyTakeaway from "../../../components/KeyTakeaway.astro";
import InfoBox from "../../../components/InfoBox.astro";
---

<Article
  title="Is Wyrmspan Worth It? An Honest Review for Wingspan Fans"
  description="If you love Wingspan, should you buy Wyrmspan? We break down the differences honestly."
  game="wyrmspan"
  gameTitle="Wyrmspan"
  category="Buying Guide"
  product="wyrmspan-resource-tokens"
  publishDate="2025-05-06"
>
  <p>
    Wyrmspan launched with massive expectations — it's the dragon-themed
    standalone game from the Wingspan universe. But is it worth the price
    if you already own Wingspan?
  </p>

  <KeyTakeaway answer="Yes, if you want a deeper, more strategic version of Wingspan's engine-building. No, if you want more of the same cozy bird experience." />

  <h2>The Verdict at a Glance</h2>

  <div class="my-6 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
    <div class="p-5 bg-emerald-50 rounded-xl border border-emerald-200">
      <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-emerald-800 mb-3">✅ Buy It If...</h4>
      <ul class="text-sm text-emerald-700/70 space-y-2">
        <li>• You've played Wingspan 20+ times and want more depth</li>
        <li>• You enjoy the engine-building core but wish it was tighter</li>
        <li>• The dragon theme excites your group</li>
        <li>• You want less dice randomness in your food/resources</li>
        <li>• You enjoy exploration mechanics</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="p-5 bg-red-50 rounded-xl border border-red-200">
      <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-red-800 mb-3">❌ Skip It If...</h4>
      <ul class="text-sm text-red-700/70 space-y-2">
        <li>• You haven't exhausted Wingspan + expansions yet</li>
        <li>• Your group prefers lighter, more accessible games</li>
        <li>• The bird theme and educational aspect is a big draw</li>
        <li>• You don't want to learn a new system</li>
        <li>• Budget is tight (get a Wingspan expansion instead)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>What Wyrmspan Does Better</h2>

  <div class="my-6 space-y-3">
    <div class="p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700 text-[11px] font-bold rounded-full">BETTER</span>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-bark">Less Randomness</h4>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">No dice-based food. You have more control over your resources, which makes planning rewarding instead of frustrating.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700 text-[11px] font-bold rounded-full">BETTER</span>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-bark">Exploration Mechanic</h4>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">The cave exploration gives you meaningful choices Wingspan doesn't have. Do you push deep for big rewards or build wide?</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700 text-[11px] font-bold rounded-full">BETTER</span>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-bark">Tighter Game Arc</h4>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">Games feel like they end at the right time. Wingspan sometimes drags in round 4; Wyrmspan's pacing stays engaging throughout.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>What Wingspan Does Better</h2>

  <div class="my-6 space-y-3">
    <div class="p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 text-[11px] font-bold rounded-full">WINGSPAN WINS</span>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-bark">Accessibility</h4>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">Wingspan is easier to teach and more welcoming to non-gamers. The bird theme is universally appealing; dragons skew more niche.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 text-[11px] font-bold rounded-full">WINGSPAN WINS</span>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-bark">Expansion Ecosystem</h4>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">Wingspan has 3 major expansions, each excellent. Wyrmspan is still building its expansion library.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 text-[11px] font-bold rounded-full">WINGSPAN WINS</span>
        <h4 class="font-heading font-semibold text-sm text-bark">Art & Production</h4>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">Wingspan's bird art is among the best in board gaming. Wyrmspan is beautiful too, but the bird cards set a nearly impossible standard.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <InfoBox type="tip" title="The Best of Both Worlds">
    Many groups own both and choose based on the session. Wingspan for a relaxed evening with mixed experience levels. Wyrmspan when the table wants to think harder. They scratch different itches despite sharing DNA.
  </InfoBox>
</Article>
